column1: 🚨BREAKING: Our Phase 3 coronavirus emergency relief bill just passed the House. Here's what it means for families and workers in Eastern Washington. We're in this together! https://t.co/kqfw56mFTW

This is the action we need to take to support #smallbiz & families living paycheck-to-paycheck. @VP says here the average family of 4 will receive $3000 in Phase 3 of the coronavirus response. https://t.co/aS26zzILTW

It’s 3.21 & #WorldDownSyndromeDay. We may be socially distant but I’m thinking of all the amazing talented passionate and inspiring people with Down syndrome I’ve had the chance to meet. My family & I send our love!
BREAKING 🚨 Phase II of our coronavirus response is headed to @POTUS’s desk. More relief and help to come. https://t.co/cT3m48z4vo
The @WhiteHouse and @CDCGov announced these guidelines today. Stay in the know on the next 15 days to slow the spread of #coronavirus. https://t.co/NhsvRcfmyN

Today is a #nationaldayofprayer for Americans affected by the #coronavirus. We’ll get through it together. There's a lot of unknowns & that's the most difficult part. Join me in praying for wisdom insight comfort and revelation.
My statement on the Families First #Coronavirus Response Act: https://t.co/4IQIXUG630

Important 🧵from @AjitPaiFCC. We need to #KeepAmericansConnected during the #coronavirus response. Thanks to everyone who is taking this pledge and stepping up for reliable broadband and telephone connectivity. ⤵️ https://t.co/4CIaUQeESb

China won't waste any chance to smear America freedom & all that we stand for.   Here's a look at their propaganda machine to blame us for the #coronavirus. They're using a global crisis to get ahead & make America look weak. Don't be fooled.   https://t.co/agfaZsyatG
⚠️ Be wary of #coronavirus scams online.   I asked @Amazon about this last week in our @HouseCommerce subcommittee hearing about fake and counterfeit products. https://t.co/JGx3WXhvtW
Here are @CDCgov resources on how to help stop the spread of #coronavirus. #COVID19   KEY: Wash your hands & stay home if you are sick. https://t.co/VlGILHrkta
I’ll be on the radio with @jasonrantz this afternoon to talk about the @VP’s visit to WA state and how we are responding to the #coronavirus threat. Tune in to @770KTTH.

#Coronavirus Update: @POTUS signed critical resources into law this AM for America respond and protect people from the #coronavirus. As the @VP told us in WA yesterday the Trump administration is committed to bringing the necessary resources to help. https://t.co/GNKK2ToZlz

I’m with my Washington state colleagues in Congress. We’re headed back to WA with @SeemaCMS & @CDCDirector. We will join @VP Mike Pence this afternoon to meet with @GovInslee and make sure everything is being done to protect people from #coronavirus. https://t.co/DgwCskeyzM

Important #coronavirus update: The House took bipartisan action to send more resources to states and communities to combat the virus + @CDCgov awarded Washington state approx $2.8 million for public health prevention & testing.

I’m closely following & monitoring the cases of #coronavirus in Washington state. The @CDCgov is advising everyone to be extra diligent about washing hands covering coughs & sneezes and staying home if you're feeling sick. Be informed & learn more here: https://t.co/5Squxx71zs

If you missed my interview this AM on @MorningsMaria catch it here. We talked the latest on impeachment containing the coronavirus #USMCA and the second phase of @POTUS’ deal with China. https://t.co/VRnImbO3EO
